
1. Compiling the Code
To make the executable file for running the NDOT models, use the following command:

g++ -fopenmp functions.cpp main_code.cpp -o job.out

2. Running the Code
Once the compilation is successful, you can run the code by executing the following:


./job.out

3. Simulations for CaGP, DCP, and CaCO3
For simulations involving CaGP, DCP, or CaCO3, follow these steps:

Modify the calcium and phosphate concentrations in the ion.txt file.

Then, follow the same procedure for compiling and running the code as mentioned above.

4. Output Files
The output will be written to the following files:

Files starting with all_ion: These will store the ion concentration as a function of time.

Files starting with remin_demin: These will store the porosity of the enamel as a function of time.

5. Changing Parameters
If you need to make any adjustments to the simulation parameters, you can do so by editing the parameter.h file. Be sure to make any necessary changes before running the simulation.
